				Daily CSS Challenge is a great way to build CSS drawing skills. Every day you receive a prompt to create an image using only HTML and CSS. It starts out with a simple image and a thorough tutorial that walks you through the creating process step by step. After that you're left with your own creativity and the help of the community that was built around this challenge (mostly Facebook group and the #dailycssimages hashtag on Twitter).  I tried out this challenge in for a little over a week. It was fun in the beginning because it was a new concept which required developing of a new set of skills, but after a while the prompts became a little repetitive and I decided I had other things to do that will benefit me better. Also, I am not really an artists, so it bothered me that I could get as efficient in drawing shapes as I can ever be, but it will never look great because I simply can't draw.

